job_description:
Tasks •Preparing tender documents;

Negotiating with suppliers and awarding contracts;
Identifying and realizing potential savings;
Constantly reviewing and optimizing the supplier portfolio;
Positioning and using our customer attractiveness during purchasing negotiations;
Advising internal customers on requirements and feasibility;
Optimizing purchase processes;
Assuring high-quality standards through provisioning and monitoring of relevant key figures;
Observing market development (product innovation, raw materials) and act accordingly.
Strengths •You have obtained a degree in Business Administration or comparable and have gained experience in the field of purchasing;

You possess strong English and German language skills;
You think and act constantly in a 'customer', 'cost' and 'product-oriented way;
You are able to take full advantage of your strong negotiation, communication, team working and problem-solving skills;
You know when and how to balance assertiveness and diplomacy;
You are resilient and flexible;
You can work independently and structured;
You possess strong MS Office skills, especially Excel / (knowledge of SAP is an advantage).
Salary & Benefits
Fair salary for permanent and temporary employees as well as appropriate compensation for internships
Collective agreement with dynamic salary development
Attractive company pension scheme with 2/3 employer contribution
Disability insurance to cover you until you retire
Reimbursement of travel costs for the daily commute (up to 45 km each way)
Reduced health insurance contributions through collective agreements
Legal entitlement to up to 5 weeks paternity leave
Financial support in the event of a necessary relocation
About us Progress in responsibility for our customers. - this is the brand promise of Europe's largest mail-order pharmacy and Germany's best-known pharmacy brand. As a pharmacy with a comprehensive range of services, DocMorris stands for nationwide safe and high-quality pharmaceutical care. For the subsidiaries of the Swiss Zur Rose Group AG, more than 1800 employees work all over Germany in a highly dynamic, international environment on the claim to be drivers and pioneers of patient-oriented and innovative eHealth applications.
Contact We look forward to receiving your application! If you have any questions, please contact Gianni Crisafulli at 0031 45 201 7159.
